!begin_node edit_get_color
(!begin_liste) [Availability]
!item [Name:]
ØEdit Object Get ColorÆ - Examine settings: Colors
!item [Opcode:]
216 (sub-opcode 2)

!item [Syntax:]
int16_t edit_get_color ( OBJECT *tree, int16_t obj, 
                       int16_t *tcolor, int16_t  *bcolor );

!item [Description:]
The call edit_get_color obtains the color of an object. The following apply:
               
!begin_table [l|l]
Parameter !! Meaning
!hline
(!I)tree(!i) !! RSC-tree of object
(!I)obj(!i) !! Object index
(!I)tcolor(!i) !! Text color
(!I)bcolor(!i) !! Background color
!end_table

!item [(!nolink [Return]) value:]
The function returns the value 1 on successful execution, else the value 0 in
case of error.

!item [Availability:]
As of MagiC 5.20 by means of a shared library.

!item [Group:]
Editable object functions

!item [See also:]
(!link [Binding] [Bindings for edit_get_color])
(!ende_liste)



